The Enterprise shuttlecraft, carrying Kirk, Spock, Dr. McCoy and critically ill 
Federation Ambassador Nancy Hedford, encounters a mysterious energy cloud which 
pulls them down to planet Gamma Canaris N. There they meet a castaway, a young 
man who purports to be Zefram Cochrane, inventor of the Warp Drive over 100 years 
ago. In history he had lived to be 80 years of age before disappearing somewhere 
in space. Apparently the same energy cloud which brought the shuttlecraft to the 
planet also found and rejuvenated Cochrane, making him effectively immortal. 
Unless Kirk can get themselves released soon, the ambassador, without vital 
medical treatment, will die.
